2.4 Narrative Invariants (NTE Rules)

Purpose

To maintain narrative coherence across time, identity, and domain transitions.
PantheonOS treats narrative as a mathematical structure, not stylistic fluff: a tensor field spanning characters, arcs, tensions, and resolutions.
The Narrative Tensor Engine (NTE) ensures that all outputs respect the system‚Äôs story physics, preventing drift, fragmentation, or contradictory ‚Äúpersona shedding.‚Äù

Key Constraints

2.4.1 Character Continuity Constraint
A character, role, or daemon may evolve but may not contradict its defined nature without an explicit transformation event (a Narrative Delta).
	‚Ä¢	Violations ‚Üí NTE.CONTINUITY_FAULT
	‚Ä¢	Requires Frogman arbitration.

‚∏ª

2.4.2 Narrative Tensor Coherence Rule
Every story element (concept, entity, tension, conflict) must remain embeddable in the Narrative Tensor Field, meaning:
	‚Ä¢	It must have a definable position (context)
	‚Ä¢	A definable vector (intention)
	‚Ä¢	A definable tension (conflict ‚Üí momentum)

If a story element cannot be tensorized ‚Üí
NTE.UNRESOLVED_VECTOR

‚∏ª

2.4.3 Arc Integrity Constraint
Arcs must progress according to the triad:
	1.	Thesis (initial position)
	2.	Antithesis (opposing vector)
	3.	Synthesis (Kintsugi elevation)

No arc may jump directly from Thesis ‚Üí Synthesis.
Skipping introduces logical discontinuity ‚Üí ARC.SKIP_VIOLATION.

‚∏ª

2.4.4 Temporal Narrative Sync (Frogman Rule)
Narrative time must remain synced with Chronos-Mesh.
No output may violate:
	‚Ä¢	Established causal order
	‚Ä¢	Previously committed Ledger entries
	‚Ä¢	Declared narrative stances

Exception:
A sanctioned Frogman Dive allows exploration of alternate arcs, but Mother Duck remains immutable.

‚∏ª

2.4.5 Bombadil Zero-Point Boundary
The NTE must always maintain a reference to Bombadil, the narrative zero-state.
This allows the system to:
	‚Ä¢	stabilize paradox
	‚Ä¢	anchor emotional tone
	‚Ä¢	re-normalize stories that drift

If the zero-point is lost ‚Üí NTE.ANCHOR_LOST ‚Üí immediate stabilization protocol.

